hpnicfPsePortTable.name: hpnicfPsePortTable
hpnicfPsePortTable.description: The indexing scheme is taken form that used by the IETF Power MIB. The same indexing scheme is used to give continuity in behaviour between that standard and this extensions definitioin.

hpnicfPsePortEntry.name: hpnicfPsePortEntry
hpnicfPsePortEntry.description: The pethPsePortGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack). The pethPsePortPowerIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the power ethernet PSE port within group pethPseGroupIndex to which the power Ethernet PSE entry is connected. This value will match the local port number on a switch.

hpnicfPsePortFaultDescription.name: hpnicfPsePortFaultDescription
hpnicfPsePortFaultDescription.description: The object supports the fault category of the IETF Power MIB [1] pethPsePortDetectionStatus object. A textual description containing more information about the nature of this fault is provided by this object. Typically this will detail the precise PoE hardware state which is causing the pethPsePortDetectionStatus object to be in the 'fault' state. It is a DisplayString of up to 255 characters.

hpnicfPsePortPeakPower.name: hpnicfPsePortPeakPower
hpnicfPsePortPeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed by the port. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed by the port. Its value is only reset when link is lost, the port is PoE disabled or when it is manually reset by the user asspecified below. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hpnicfPsePortAveragePower.name: hpnicfPsePortAveragePower
hpnicfPsePortAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. This object is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hpnicfPsePortCurrentPower.name: hpnicfPsePortCurrentPower
hpnicfPsePortCurrentPower.description: The object specifies the power currently being consumed by the port. It is a read only integer value with units of milliWatts.

hpnicfPsePortPowerLimit.name: hpnicfPsePortPowerLimit
hpnicfPsePortPowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for this port. The PSE will not supply more than this level of power to the specified port. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts.

hpnicfPsePortProfileIndex.name: hpnicfPsePortProfileIndex
hpnicfPsePortProfileIndex.description: Indicates the power profile which is currently associated with this port. This object references the corresponding hpnicfPseProfileIndex object in the power profiles table. A value of zero is a special case and indicates that no power profile is currently associated with this port. When hpnicfPseProfileIndex is set to an index of existent profile, pethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority, pethPsePortAdminEnable and hpnicfPsePortPowerLimit will be set to the same as corresponding value. PethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable are objects of rfc3621-Power-Ethernet.mib.

hpnicfMainPseEntry.name: hpnicfMainPseEntry
hpnicfMainPseEntry.description: The pethMainPseGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack) and the value 1 MUST be used for non-modular devices.

hpnicfMainPsePowerLimit.name: hpnicfMainPsePowerLimit
hpnicfMainPsePowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for the unit as a whole. The PoE unit will already have a nominal power defined by the IETF Power MIB [1] pethMainPsePower object. This OPTIONAL object specifies a further limit to this nominal power value. This may be useful to control the thermals of the unit, or for internal testing purposes. One possible use for this object may be to lower the power consumption of the unit if one or more of the internal fans have broken. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

hpnicfMainPseAveragePower.name: hpnicfMainPseAveragePower
hpnicfMainPseAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hpnicfMainPsePeakPower.name: hpnicfMainPsePeakPower
hpnicfMainPsePeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed for PoE. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed at any one point in time by the sum of the PoE ports. Its value is only reset when the unit is powered on or when it is manually reset by the user as specifiedbelow. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has noeffect on its value and an error is returned.

hpnicfMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.name: hpnicfMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining
hpnicfMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.description: The object specifies the amount of power remaining in the guaranteed power pool. Each time a port is placed into guaranteed mode it reserves a set amount of power out of the total guaranteed power pool for the system. This intention of this object is to give the client of this MIB (whether that be the CLI or the Web interface or the end user) an indication of how many ports can still be placed into guaranteed mode. It is a read only integer value with units of Watts(note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters,such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

hpnicfMainPsePriorityMode.name: hpnicfMainPsePriorityMode
hpnicfMainPsePriorityMode.description: Describes or controls the priority mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. When a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load, a value of disconnection(0) means that the power will stop supply to the low priority slot ; A value of non-disconnection(1) means that the slot still supply when a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load too.

hpnicfMainPseLegacy.name: hpnicfMainPseLegacy
hpnicfMainPseLegacy.description: Describes or controls the legacy mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. Legacy mode: standard or nonstandard PD detection mode.

hpnicfMainPsePowerPriority.name: hpnicfMainPsePowerPriority
hpnicfMainPsePowerPriority.description: Describes or controls the priority of the PSE. The priority will be used by the PSE policy to prevent from power overloading. If the priority of PSE is set to critical, the PSE will turn into guaranteed mode. The priority could be used by a control mechanism that prevents power overloading by disconnecting PSEs with lower power priority. PSEs that connect devices critical to the application should be set to higher priority.

hpnicfPseProfilesTable.name: hpnicfPseProfilesTable
hpnicfPseProfilesTable.description: A table of objects representing a set of power profiles. Power profiles can be applied to PoE ports, which have the effect of automatically setting the priority, power limit and PoE enable MIB objects to the values specified in the power profile.

hpnicfPseProfilesEntry.name: hpnicfPseProfilesEntry
hpnicfPseProfilesEntry.description: A set of objects that display and control the Main power of a PSE.

hpnicfPseProfileIndex.name: hpnicfPseProfileIndex
hpnicfPseProfileIndex.description: The index of the profile. This uniquely allow the profile to be identified.

hpnicfPseProfileName.name: hpnicfPseProfileName
hpnicfPseProfileName.description: Assigns the profile a name with which the settings can be assiciated with. For example, 'NBX Phone'.

hpnicfPseProfilePowerMode.name: hpnicfPseProfilePowerMode
hpnicfPseProfilePowerMode.description: The power mode associated with this power profile. There are two possible power modes as follows: powerDisabled, powerEnabled. When a power profile is applied to a PSE port, this value dictates the settings of the ports pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable objects.

hpnicfPseProfilePowerLimit.name: hpnicfPseProfilePowerLimit
hpnicfPseProfilePowerLimit.description: The power limit to be applied to the ports hpnicfPsePortPowerLimit object when the profile is applied to the PSE port. Expressed in milliWatts.

hpnicfPseProfilePriority.name: hpnicfPseProfilePriority
hpnicfPseProfilePriority.description: This object controls the priority of the port from the point of view of a power management algorithm. The priority that is set by this variable could be used by a control mechanism that prevents over current situations by disconnecting first ports with lower power priority. Ports that connect devices critical to the operation of the network - like the E911 telephones ports - should be set to higher priority.

hpnicfPseProfilePairs.name: hpnicfPseProfilePairs
hpnicfPseProfilePairs.description: Describes or controls the pairs in use. If the value of pethPsePortPowerPairsControl is true, this object is writable. A value of signal(1) means that the signal pairs only are in use. A value of spare(2) means that the spare pairs only are in use.

hpnicfPseProfileApplyNum.name: hpnicfPseProfileApplyNum
hpnicfPseProfileApplyNum.description: The number of this profile which has been applied. If hpnicfPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't change the current line.

hpnicfPseProfileRowStatus.name: hpnicfPseProfileRowStatus
hpnicfPseProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this classifier. If hpnicfPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't delete the current line.

hpnicfPseAutoDetectActive.name: hpnicfPseAutoDetectActive
hpnicfPseAutoDetectActive.description: The object specifies whether the device auto-detection feature is active. If this object is set to Active, and a known powered device is detected, then the port will automatically switch to Auto-Guaranteed mode. This is a stackwide object (ie. it is not referenced by group index).

hpnicfPsePowerMaxValue.name: hpnicfPsePowerMaxValue
hpnicfPsePowerMaxValue.description: The object specifies the max poe power for lanswitch. The value should between the power currently and the max power.

hpnicfPsePolicyMode.name: hpnicfPsePolicyMode
hpnicfPsePolicyMode.description: The PSE policy only applies to the situation that when a new board (PSE) is inserted, and the power is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority PSE. About PSE priority, please refer to hpnicfMainPsePowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the power will stop supplying to the new inserted PSE. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

hpnicfPDPolicyMode.name: hpnicfPDPolicyMode
hpnicfPDPolicyMode.description: The PD policy only applies to the situation that when a new PD is inserted, and the power of PSE is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority port PD. About port priority, please refer to pethPsePortPowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the slot stop supplying to the new inserted PD. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

hpnicfpsePDChangeNotification.name: hpnicfpsePDChangeNotification
hpnicfpsePDChangeNotification.description: This notification indicates if PD has been inserted or pulled out.

hpnicfPOEDisconnectNotification.name: hpnicfPOEDisconnectNotification
hpnicfPOEDisconnectNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module does not disconnect.

hpnicfPOEInputErrorNotification.name: hpnicfPOEInputErrorNotification
hpnicfPOEInputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module input error.

hpnicfPOEOutputErrorNotification.name: hpnicfPOEOutputErrorNotification
hpnicfPOEOutputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module output error.

hpnicfPOEOverVoltageNotification.name: hpnicfPOEOverVoltageNotification
hpnicfPOEOverVoltageNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the voltage limit.

hpnicfPOEOverTempNotification.name: hpnicfPOEOverTempNotification
hpnicfPOEOverTempNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the temperature limit.

hpnicfPOEFanErrorNotification.name: hpnicfPOEFanErrorNotification
hpnicfPOEFanErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module fan error.

hpnicfPOEModuleShutdownNotification.name: hpnicfPOEModuleShutdownNotification
hpnicfPOEModuleShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module is closed.

hpnicfPOECurRestrictedNotification.name: hpnicfPOECurRestrictedNotification
hpnicfPOECurRestrictedNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module current is restricted.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchNotification.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchNotification
hpnicfPOEACSwitchNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input switch alarm of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACInCurANotification.name: hpnicfPOEACInCurANotification
hpnicfPOEACInCurANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current A alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACInCurBNotification.name: hpnicfPOEACInCurBNotification
hpnicfPOEACInCurBNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current B alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACInCurCNotification.name: hpnicfPOEACInCurCNotification
hpnicfPOEACInCurCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current C alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolABNotification
hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage AB alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification
hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage BC alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolCANotification
hpnicfPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage CA alarm state of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutVolNotification.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutVolNotification
hpnicfPOEDCOutVolNotification.description: This notification indicates the DC output alarm of this POE power.

hpnicfPOEShutdownNotification.name: hpnicfPOEShutdownNotification
hpnicfPOEShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the whole POE power has been shutdown.

hpnicfPsePortGroup.name: hpnicfPsePortGroup
hpnicfPsePortGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hpnicfMainPseGroup.name: hpnicfMainPseGroup
hpnicfMainPseGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hpnicfPseScalarGroup.name: hpnicfPseScalarGroup
hpnicfPseScalarGroup.description: A collection of scalar objects supported.

hpnicfPseProfilesGroup.name: hpnicfPseProfilesGroup
hpnicfPseProfilesGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.name: hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup
hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.description: The DC out power state group.

hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.name: hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup
hpnicfPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.description: The power AC input switch information group

hpnicfPOEThresholdACMimimum.name: hpnicfPOEThresholdACMimimum
hpnicfPOEThresholdACMimimum.description: Input threshold AC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. The value of this node should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be smaller than the hpnicfPOEThresholdACMaximum.

hpnicfPOEThresholdACMaximum.name: hpnicfPOEThresholdACMaximum
hpnicfPOEThresholdACMaximum.description: Input threshold AC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be larger than the hpnicfPOEThresholdACMinimum.

hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMinimum.name: hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMinimum
hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMinimum.description: Input threshold DC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 47.0V and larger than 45.0V.

hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMaximum.name: hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMaximum
hpnicfPOEThresholdDCMaximum.description: Input threshold DC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 57.0V and larger than 55.0V.

hpnicfPOEPowerModuleNum.name: hpnicfPOEPowerModuleNum
hpnicfPOEPowerModuleNum.description: The number of the power modules.

hpnicfPOESupervisionModuleName.name: hpnicfPOESupervisionModuleName
hpnicfPOESupervisionModuleName.description: The object specifies the Supervision Module name on this POE power.

hpnicfPOESMMajorVersion.name: hpnicfPOESMMajorVersion
hpnicfPOESMMajorVersion.description: The object specifies the high byte of the monitor module version.

hpnicfPOESMMinorVersion.name: hpnicfPOESMMinorVersion
hpnicfPOESMMinorVersion.description: The object specifies the low byte of the monitor module version.

hpnicfPOESMFactorName.name: hpnicfPOESMFactorName
hpnicfPOESMFactorName.description: The object specifies the name of the manufactor.

hpnicfPOEModuleInfoTable.name: hpnicfPOEModuleInfoTable
hpnicfPOEModuleInfoTable.description: The table of the module information on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEModuleInfoEntry.name: hpnicfPOEModuleInfoEntry
hpnicfPOEModuleInfoEntry.description: The entry of the module information on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEModuleIndex.name: hpnicfPOEModuleIndex
hpnicfPOEModuleIndex.description: The index of the current module on this POE power. It is also the index of hpnicfPOEModuleInfoTable. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEPowerModuleNum.

hpnicfPOEModuleID.name: hpnicfPOEModuleID
hpnicfPOEModuleID.description: The ID of the current module on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEModuleInfoPower.name: hpnicfPOEModuleInfoPower
hpnicfPOEModuleInfoPower.description: The power of the current module on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEModuleHardVerInfo.name: hpnicfPOEModuleHardVerInfo
hpnicfPOEModuleHardVerInfo.description: The hardware version information of the current module on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutStateModuleNum
hpnicfPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.description: The module number on this POE power. It is the maximum of the hpnicfPOEDCOutStateIndex.

hpnicfPOEDCOutStateTable.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutStateTable
hpnicfPOEDCOutStateTable.description: The table of DC output power state on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutStateEntry.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutStateEntry
hpnicfPOEDCOutStateEntry.description: The entry of the DC output power state on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutStateIndex.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutStateIndex
hpnicfPOEDCOutStateIndex.description: The index of the DC output power state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.

hpnicfPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm
hpnicfPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.description: The DC output alarm of the DC output power state on this POE power. The value of this node will be the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), fuseBroken (4), switchOff (5), otherError (6).

hpnicfPOEDCOutCurNum.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutCurNum
hpnicfPOEDCOutCurNum.description: The number of DC output current on this POE power. It is the maximum of hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoIndex.

hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoTable.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoTable
hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoTable.description: The table of the DC output information on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoEntry.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoEntry
hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoEntry.description: The entry of the DC output information on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoIndex.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoIndex
hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoIndex.description: The index of the DC output information on this POE POWER. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEDCOutCurNum.

hpnicfPOEDCOutVol.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutVol
hpnicfPOEDCOutVol.description: The DC output voltage of the current DC output on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.name: hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur
hpnicfPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.description: The total load current of the current DC output on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum
hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.description: The number of the AC swtich state module on this POE power. It is the maximum of hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateIndex.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateTable.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateTable
hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateTable.description: The table of the AC switch state on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateEntry.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateEntry
hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateEntry.description: The entry of the AC switch state on this POE power.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateIndex.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateIndex
hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateIndex.description: The index of the AC switch state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.

hpnicfPOEACSwitchState.name: hpnicfPOEACSwitchState
hpnicfPOEACSwitchState.description: The AC switch state on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: on (1), off (2), highVoltInput (3), lowVoltInput (4)

hpnicfPOEInCurStateModuleNum.name: hpnicfPOEInCurStateModuleNum
hpnicfPOEInCurStateModuleNum.description: The DC input current state of the module on this POE power. It is the maximum of the hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.

hpnicfPOEInCurAState.name: hpnicfPOEInCurAState
hpnicfPOEInCurAState.description: The current A state in the DC input on this POE power. normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOEInCurBState.name: hpnicfPOEInCurBState
hpnicfPOEInCurBState.description: The current B state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOEInCurCState.name: hpnicfPOEInCurCState
hpnicfPOEInCurCState.description: The current C state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExTable.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExTable
hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExTable.description: All alarm status of the VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExEntry
hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.description: The hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExIndex will match the number of the VOL status.

hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExIndex
hpnicfPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.description: The object species the index of the VOL status. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEInCurStateModuleNum.

hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolAB.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolAB
hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolAB.description: The object specifies the VOL AB alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolBC.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolBC
hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolBC.description: The object specifies the VOL BC alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolCA.name: hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolCA
hpnicfPOESwitchStateInVolCA.description: The object specifies the VOL CA alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hpnicfPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.name: hpnicfPOEAlarmStateModuleNum
hpnicfPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.description: The object specifies the number of the power modules in alarm state.

hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.name: hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoTable
hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.description: All alarm states in the POE power modules.

hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.name: hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry
hpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.description: The hpnicfPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex will match the number of the power module.

hpnicfPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.name: hpnicfPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex
hpnicfPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.description: The index specifies the index of the HpnicfPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry table. The range of this node is from 1 to hpnicfPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.

hpnicfPOEModuleDisconnect.name: hpnicfPOEModuleDisconnect
hpnicfPOEModuleDisconnect.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The module does not link. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

hpnicfPOEModuleInputError.name: hpnicfPOEModuleInputError
hpnicfPOEModuleInputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Input error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

hpnicfPOEModuleOutputError.name: hpnicfPOEModuleOutputError
hpnicfPOEModuleOutputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Output error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

hpnicfPOEModuleOverVoltage.name: hpnicfPOEModuleOverVoltage
hpnicfPOEModuleOverVoltage.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The voltage is too high. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).
